* He searched around the crashed ship and all he could really find were the 
dead bodies of his crew members, feeling slight regret on accepting this 
mission but how was he to know that this was going to happen?
It was a simple construction assignment, that was it. Same as hundreds  of 
ones they'd done before. But this one had ended with desaster and now he 
didn't even know where he was.
#1) was because he was blind
#2) was because none of his systems had come online yet, none of the 
tracking or navigational ones anyway
And that was about it.
So, now he was on his own and with the scents of the dead and leaking fuel, 
he really didn't want to stick around too much. Besides, he could already 
feel warm mech-fluid leak from his right brown and maybe he could find a bit 
of water to clean himself up with a bit.
So, with his nose stretched out ahead of him, he scurried off into the 
surrounding forest.
Probably no one expecting to see a 5ft tall mole sliding in and out of the 
shadows cast by the towering trees.*
